{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889061822,"sessionID":"ses_284c3b010ffe0LE9TcN7RMsSTZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3c939b001RIYFzAYOF9gNxt","messageID":"msg_d7b3c7086001gfhsegawI7E56l","sessionID":"ses_284c3b010ffe0LE9TcN7RMsSTZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a8af260b7d3843e9b9306573","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-038: Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers comprehensive Go unit tests for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module, including handler, middleware, reconciler, response sub-packages and top-level constants.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 System Context\n10: \n11: ```\n12: pkg/workloadmanager/\n13: ├── const.go              # Constants/enums\n14: ├── const_test.go         # NEW — constant validation tests\n15: ├── handler/\n16: │   ├── *.go              # HTTP handlers\n17: │   └── *_test.go         # NEW — handler tests\n18: ├── middleware/\n19: │   ├── *.go              # HTTP middleware\n20: │   └── *_test.go         # NEW — middleware tests\n21: ├── reconciler/\n22: │   ├── *.go              # State reconciler\n23: │   └── *_test.go         # NEW — reconciler tests\n24: └── response/\n25:     ├── *.go              # Response utilities\n26:     └── *_test.go         # NEW — response tests\n27: ```\n28: \n29: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n30: \n31: - **Table-driven tests**: Go idiom for test data organization\n32: - **No production code changes**: Only `*_test.go` additions\n33: - **httptest for handlers**: `net/http/httptest` for HTTP handler testing\n34: - **Interface-based mocking**: Abstract external dependencies behind interfaces\n35: - **Black-box + white-box**: Mix of `package_test` and `package_internal_test` as needed\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 2. Test Strategy by Sub-Package\n40: \n41: ### 2.1 handler/\n42: \n43: | Test Category | Approach |\n44: |---------------|----------|\n45: | Request parsing | Valid/invalid JSON, missing fields, type mismatches |\n46: | Response construction | Status codes, body format, headers |\n47: | Error handling | 4xx/5xx scenarios, panic recovery |\n48: | Edge cases | Empty body, oversized payload, concurrent requests |\n49: \n50: ### 2.2 middleware/\n51: \n52: | Test Category | Approach |\n53: |---------------|----------|\n54: | Auth middleware | Valid token, expired token, missing token, malformed token |\n55: | Logging middleware | Output capture, request ID propagation |\n56: | Validation middleware | Pass-through, rejection with error response |\n57: | Recovery middleware | Panic caught, 500 returned, stack trace logged |\n58: \n59: ### 2.3 reconciler/\n60: \n61: | Test Category | Approach |\n62: |---------------|----------|\n63: | State sync | Current vs desired state convergence |\n64: | Retry logic | Max retries, backoff, success after retry |\n65: | Idempotency | Repeated calls produce same result |\n66: | Error propagation | Dependency failure handling |\n67: \n68: ### 2.4 response/\n69: \n70: | Test Category | Approach |\n71: |---------------|----------|\n72: | JSON serialization | Struct → JSON, nil fields, special characters |\n73: | Error code mapping | Internal error → HTTP status, custom codes |\n74: | Helper functions | Response writers, header setting |\n75: \n76: ### 2.5 const.go\n77: \n78: | Test Category | Approach |\n79: |---------------|----------|\n80: | Enum completeness | All expected values present |\n81: | Boundary conditions | Min/max values, zero values |\n82: | String representations | `String()` methods (if any) |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## 3. Testing Patterns\n87: \n88: ### 3.1 Table-Driven Test Template\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: func TestHandler_Foo(t *testing.T) {\n92:     tests := []struct {\n93:         name       string\n94:         input      RequestType\n95:         wantStatus int\n96:         wantBody   string\n97:         wantErr    bool\n98:     }{\n99:         {\n100:             name:       \"valid request\",\n101:             input:      RequestType{Field: \"value\"},\n102:             wantStatus: http.StatusOK,\n103:             wantBody:   `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`,\n104:             wantErr:    false,\n105:         },\n106:         {\n107:             name:       \"invalid request\",\n108:             input:      RequestType{},\n109:             wantStatus: http.StatusBadRequest,\n110:             wantBody:   `{\"error\":\"...\"}`,\n111:             wantErr:    true,\n112:         },\n113:     }\n114: \n115:     for _, tt := range tests {\n116:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n117:             // Arrange\n118:             req := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodPost, \"/path\", toJSON(tt.input))\n119:             w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n120: \n121:             // Act\n122:             handler(w, req)\n123: \n124:             // Assert\n125:             assert.Equal(t, tt.wantStatus, w.Code)\n126:             if tt.wantBody != \"\" {\n127:                 assert.JSONEq(t, tt.wantBody, w.Body.String())\n128:             }\n129:         })\n130:     }\n131: }\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ### 3.2 Mock Pattern\n135: \n136: ```go\n137: type mockDependency struct {\n138:     // Record calls\n139:     calls []string\n140:     // Configure behavior\n141:     err error\n142: }\n143: \n144: func (m *mockDependency) DoSomething() error {\n145:     m.calls = append(m.calls, \"DoSomething\")\n146:     return m.err\n147: }\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 4. Coverage Targets\n153: \n154: | Sub-Package | Target Coverage | Rationale |\n155: |-------------|-----------------|-----------|\n156: | handler/ | 80%+ | Core user-facing logic |\n157: | middleware/ | 85%+ | Critical path, many edge cases |\n158: | reconciler/ | 75%+ | Complex state machine |\n159: | response/ | 90%+ | Simple utilities, should be fully covered |\n160: | const.go | 100% | Trivial but important |\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## 5. Implementation Notes\n165: \n166: - Use `go test -cover` to measure coverage\n167: - Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` to execute all tests\n168: - No external services required — all dependencies mocked\n169: - Tests should be deterministic (no flaky tests)\n\n(End of file - total 169 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-038: Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers comprehensive Go unit tests for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module, including handler, middleware, reconciler, response sub-packages and top-level constants.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── const.go              # Constants/enums\n├── const_test.go         # NEW — constant validation tests\n├── handler/\n│   ├── *.go              # HTTP handlers\n│   └── *_test.go         # NEW — handler tests\n├── middleware/\n│   ├── *.go              # HTTP middleware\n│   └── *_test.go         # NEW — middleware tests","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/design.md","time":{"start":1775889061812,"end":1775889061821}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889063057,"sessionID":"ses_284c3b010ffe0LE9TcN7RMsSTZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3c987300104SogRrnAdhfy0","messageID":"msg_d7b3c7086001gfhsegawI7E56l","sessionID":"ses_284c3b010ffe0LE9TcN7RMsSTZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c932317a9e554f339076e979","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-038/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-038: Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager) — Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager` | **Language:** Go | **Size:** L\n4: **Base specs:** `pkg/workloadmanager/` source code\n5: **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## T-1: handler/sandbox_create.go — CreateSandboxRequest validation\n10: \n11: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create_test.go`\n12: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — valid request passes\n13: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — empty `Name` returns error\n14: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — empty `Namespace` returns error\n15: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — empty `Kind` returns error\n16: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — missing required `Template` fields returns error\n17: - [ ] Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` — invalid port range (negative, >65535) returns error\n18: - [ ] Test `generateSessionID()` — returns valid UUID format\n19: - [ ] Test `generateSessionID()` — uniqueness across multiple calls\n20: - [ ] Test `generateSandboxName()` — follows naming convention with prefix + random suffix\n21: - [ ] Test `RandString(n)` — returns string of exact length `n`\n22: - [ ] Test `RandString(n)` — contains only alphanumeric characters\n23: - [ ] Test `getPortsOrDefaults()` — uses template ports when present\n24: - [ ] Test `getPortsOrDefaults()` — applies defaults when template ports are empty\n25: - [ ] Test `getPortsOrDefaults()` — mixed: some ports specified, others defaulted\n26: - [ ] Target: 90%+ coverage for validation and utility functions\n27: \n28: ## T-2: handler/sandbox_create.go — CR building logic\n29: \n30: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — builds valid AgentRuntime CR with all fields\n31: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — labels include `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by=agentcube`\n32: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — labels include session-id and workload-name\n33: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — annotations include idle-timeout when specified\n34: - [ ] Test `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR()` — entry points populated from request\n35: - [ ] Test `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR()` — builds valid CodeInterpreter CR\n36: - [ ] Test `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR()` — warm pool branch: sets warm pool annotations/labels\n37: - [ ] Test `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR()` — non-warm-pool branch: omits warm pool fields\n38: - [ ] Test `buildEntryPoints()` — converts port specs to EntryPoint slice\n39: - [ ] Test `buildEntryPoints()` — handles empty ports list\n40: - [ ] Target: 85%+ coverage for CR building functions\n41: \n42: ## T-3: handler/sandbox_create.go — PicoD auth and Pod IP resolution\n43: \n44: - [ ] Test `injectPicodAuthEnv()` — injects identity secret env vars into container spec\n45: - [ ] Test `injectPicodAuthEnv()` — uses correct secret name `picod-router-identity` and key `public.pem`\n46: - [ ] Test `injectPicodAuthEnv()` — handles containers with existing env vars (appends, not replaces)\n47: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — resolves IP from `AnnotationSandboxPodName` annotation when pod exists\n48: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — resolves IP from label selector when annotation is missing\n49: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — returns empty string when no pod found\n50: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — handles pod without IP assigned (pending state)\n51: - [ ] Test `resolvePodIP()` — uses fake dynamic client with test scheme\n52: - [ ] Target: 85%+ coverage for auth injection and IP resolution\n53: \n54: ## T-4: handler/sandbox_create.go — HTTP handler integration\n55: \n56: - [ ] Test `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` HTTP handler — valid request returns 201 with sandbox info\n57: - [ ] Test `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` — invalid JSON body returns 400\n58: - [ ] Test `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` — validation failure returns 400 with error details\n59: - [ ] Test `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` — store create error returns 500\n60: - [ ] Test `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox()` — valid request returns 201\n61: - [ ] Test `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox()` — invalid kind returns 400\n62: - [ ] Test `rollbackCR()` — deletes CR on creation failure, logs error if rollback also fails\n63: - [ ] Test `SandboxCreateHandler` constructor — initializes with required dependencies\n64: - [ ] Test response body matches `CreateSandboxResponse` JSON structure\n65: - [ ] Target: 80%+ coverage for HTTP handlers\n66: \n67: ## T-5: handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go — GC orphan CR cleanup\n68: \n69: - [ ] Add tests to `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_lifecycle_test.go`\n70: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — finds and deletes CRs without corresponding sandbox entries\n71: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — skips CRs that have valid sandbox entries\n72: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — handles empty store (no CRs to clean)\n73: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — respects `MaxOrphanScanLimit`\n74: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — records orphan cleanup metric on deletion\n75: - [ ] Test `cleanupOrphanCRs()` — handles lister error gracefully (logs, does not panic)\n76: - [ ] Test `cleanupGhostEntries()` — removes store entries for non-existent CRs\n77: - [ ] Test `cleanupGhostEntries()` — skips entries with valid CRs\n78: - [ ] Test `cleanupGhostEntries()` — handles empty store\n79: - [ ] Test `cleanupGhostEntries()` — records ghost entry cleanup metric\n80: - [ ] Target: 85%+ coverage for orphan/ghost cleanup\n81: \n82: ## T-6: handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go — TTL/idle calculation and deletion\n83: \n84: - [ ] Test `calculateTimeToIdle()` — returns correct duration from last-activity annotation\n85: - [ ] Test `calculateTimeToIdle()` — handles missing annotation (uses creation time)\n86: - [ ] Test `calculateTimeToIdle()` — handles invalid annotation format (falls back to creation time)\n87: - [ ] Test `parseIdleTimeoutFromAnnotations()` — parses valid idle timeout annotation\n88: - [ ] Test `parseIdleTimeoutFromAnnotations()` — returns default when annotation missing\n89: - [ ] Test `parseIdleTimeoutFromAnnotations()` — returns default when annotation is invalid\n90: - [ ] Test `extractIdleTimeoutFromCR()` — extracts from CR annotations\n91: - [ ] Test `extractIdleTimeoutFromCR()` — returns default for CR without annotation\n92: - [ ] Test `isIdleExpired()` — returns true when idle timeout exceeded\n93: - [ ] Test `isIdleExpired()` — returns false when within idle timeout\n94: - [ ] Test `isIdleExpired()` — boundary: exact idle timeout moment (not yet expired)\n95: - [ ] Test `deleteSandbox()` — deletes sandbox and records metric\n96: - [ ] Test `deleteSandbox()` — handles delete error gracefully\n97: - [ ] Test `resolveGVR()` — returns correct GVR for each of 4 kinds (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Sandbox, SandboxClaim)\n98: - [ ] Test `resolveGVR()` — returns error for unknown kind\n99: - [ ] Target: 90%+ coverage for TTL/idle logic\n100: \n101: ## T-7: reconciler/types.go — constants and interface tests\n102: \n103: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/types_test.go`\n104: - [ ] Test resource type constants are distinct non-empty strings\n105: - [ ] Test result constants (`resultSuccess`, `resultError`) are distinct\n106: - [ ] Test error type constants are distinct and descriptive\n107: - [ ] Test status constants (`StatusPending`, `StatusRunning`, `StatusTerminated`) are distinct\n108: - [ ] Test `maxRetries`, `defaultWorkers`, `cacheSyncTimeout`, `shutdownTimeout` have expected values\n109: - [ ] Test `Store` interface methods exist (via compilation check in integration tests)\n110: - [ ] Test `ReconcilerDeps` struct fields are correctly typed\n111: - [ ] Target: 100% coverage for constants\n112: \n113: ## T-8: reconciler/metrics.go — metric recording methods\n114: \n115: - [ ] Extend `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics_test.go`\n116: - [ ] Test `IncReconcileTotal()` — increments counter with correct labels\n117: - [ ] Test `IncReconcileTotal()` — different result types (success/error) recorded separately\n118: - [ ] Test `ObserveReconcileDuration()` — records duration histogram with correct labels\n119: - [ ] Test `IncReconcileErrors()` — increments error counter with error type label\n120: - [ ] Test `IncReconcileErrors()` — different error types recorded separately\n121: - [ ] Test `SetWorkqueueDepth()` — sets gauge to current depth value\n122: - [ ] Test `IncWorkqueueAdds()` — increments workqueue adds counter\n123: - [ ] Test `NewPrometheusMetricsRecorder(nil)` — returns recorder without panic (nil registerer)\n124: - [ ] Test `NewPrometheusMetricsRecorder(nonNil)` — registers all metrics successfully\n125: - [ ] Test all metric methods on nil receiver — no panic (nil safety)\n126: - [ ] Target: 90%+ coverage for metrics recorder\n127: \n128: ## T-9: reconciler/sync.go — workqueue processing\n129: \n130: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sync_test.go`\n131: - [ ] Test `determineResourceType()` — returns `resourceTypeAgentRuntime` for AgentRuntime object\n132: - [ ] Test `determineResourceType()` — returns `resourceTypeCodeInterpreter` for CodeInterpreter object\n133: - [ ] Test `determineResourceType()` — returns `resourceTypePod` for Pod object\n134: - [ ] Test `determineResourceType()` — returns empty for unknown GVK\n135: - [ ] Test `processNextWorkItem()` — processes item successfully, forgets from 